(1) 114–118 East 113th Street, south side, between Park and Lexington Avenue. Nos. 116 and 118 are three-story frame houses, the former with a brick front. 1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York, Negative No. 132.

(2) Another view.

July 6, 1934.

P.L. Sperr.
